  "prompt": "What is distance over time?",
  "response": "Distance over time is a measure of the speed or velocity at which an object travels. It is calculated using the formula:\n\n\\[ \\text{Speed} = \\frac{\\text{Distance}}{\\text{Time}} \\]\n\nWhere:\n- Distance is the total length of the path traveled by the object.\n- Time is the duration taken to travel that distance.\n\nFor example, if a car travels 100 kilometers in 2 hours, the speed (or velocity, if direction is considered) would be:\n\n\\[ \\text{Speed} = \\frac{100 \\text{ km}}{2 \\text{ hours}} = 50 \\text{ km/h} \\]\n\nSpeed is typically measured in units such as meters per second (m/s), kilometers per hour (km/h), or miles per hour (mph), depending on the context.",
